<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'Privacy' }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="page" id="main-content" role="main">
<section class="page-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up" style="max-width:720px;">
      <div class="section-tag">Privacy</div>
      <h2>What we know, what we don't, and what we do with it.</h2>
      <p>Privacy isn't a feature for us — it's the reason the product exists the way it does. Every design decision in perch. starts from the position that your data belongs to you, not us.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-body a-fade-up">
      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>What we process</h3>
        <p>When you forward an email or upload a document to perch., we extract the information needed to track that renewal: provider name, category, amount, renewal date, and cancellation notice period. That's it. We don't read the rest of the email. We don't store attachments beyond what's needed for extraction.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>What we never see</h3>
        <p>We never connect to your bank accounts, card accounts, or any financial institution. We never request read-only access, API tokens, or "just this once" permissions. Your transaction history, balance, and spending patterns are none of our business — literally.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>What we don't do with your data</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>We don't train AI models on your documents or extracted data.</li>
          <li>We don't sell your information to anyone. Not anonymised, not aggregated — never.</li>
          <li>We don't share your renewal data with third parties for any purpose.</li>
          <li>We don't package your data for advertisers, partners, or "insights" products.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>How long we keep it</h3>
        <p>We keep your extracted renewal items for as long as your account is active. You can delete individual items at any time, and you can delete your entire account — along with all associated data — with a single request. When you delete, it's gone from our systems within 30 days.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Security</h3>
        <p>All data in transit is encrypted via TLS 1.3. Stored data is encrypted at rest. We use infrastructure providers that are SOC 2 compliant. We don't have access to your email inbox — you forward things to us, we don't pull them.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>The status quo is broken</h3>
        <p>Most financial tools ask for far more access than they need because the data has value beyond the product — for training models, for selling insights, for building a profile on you. We think that model is fundamentally incompatible with a product that's supposed to help you take control. perch. is designed to work with the minimum information necessary, nothing more.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Changes to this policy</h3>
        <p>If we change how we handle your data, we'll tell you before it takes effect — not bury it in a terms update email you'll never read. You'll get a clear explanation of what changed and why.</p>
        <p class="privacy-muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Questions</h3>
        <p>If you want to know more about any of this — or you want to request deletion of data we might hold about you — email <a href="mailto:privacy@perch.app" style="color:var(--accent);">privacy@perch.app</a>. We'll respond within 48 hours.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
